wiki.summary: n “Can’t Tame Her,” Zara takes pride in her self-empowerment as she notes that nobody can control her but herself. On an upbeat instrumental, she uses the beat’s fast tempo to express her lyrics. This track also marks the lead single from her forthcoming studio album. On December 8, 2022, Zara first teased the instrumental in a TikTok, where she said it was time to get your playlists ready: It’s time to call your local mall, call the department stores and tell them to get their playlists ready Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: n “Can’t Tame Her,” Zara takes pride in her self-empowerment as she notes that nobody can control her but herself. On an upbeat instrumental, she uses the beat’s fast tempo to express her lyrics. This track also marks the lead single from her forthcoming studio album. On December 8, 2022, Zara first teased the instrumental in a TikTok, where she said it was time to get your playlists ready: It’s time to call your local mall, call the department stores and tell them to get their playlists ready A few days after the first teaser, on December 13, 2022, an extended snippet was uploaded on her Twitter account, along with the rehearsal for the song’s dance choreography. In the caption, she interpolated the end of her chorus: Can’t change her Can’t blame her Can’t tame her Read more on Last.fm.
